<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q25_v8_item" title="Q25_v8" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceA</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>
      Se considera la expresión 
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>.
      Tras desarrollar el producto, se obtiene
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>6</m:mn>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>.
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      ¿Cuál de las siguientes combinaciones de términos es consistente con la simplificación correcta de 
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mi>n</m:mi>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Después de desarrollar, la expresión queda 5n + 6 − 3n. Los términos con n se pueden agrupar como (5n − 3n) y el término constante es 6, por lo que esta combinación es consistente con la simplificación correcta. Además, 5n − 3n = 2n, así que el resultado final es 2n + 6.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Tras desarrollar correctamente se obtiene 5n + 6 − 3n, no 5n + 6 + 3n. El término que proviene de 3(−n) es −3n. Por eso la combinación correcta de términos semejantes es 5n − 3n, no 5n + 3n.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al desarrollar 3(2 − n), se obtiene 6 − 3n. El término constante es +6, no −6. Por eso 5n + 6 − 3n se puede escribir como (5n − 3n) + 6, pero no como (5n − 3n) − 6.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta opción falla en ambos signos. Desde 3(2 − n) se obtiene 6 − 3n, de modo que en la expresión desarrollada aparece +6 y aparece −3n. Por eso no corresponde escribir (5n + 3n) − 6.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Desarrollar el producto</strong></p>
            <p>Se parte de la expresión</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Aplicando la propiedad distributiva:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces la expresión completa queda:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Agrupar términos semejantes</strong></p>
            <p>Los términos con variable son <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> y <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. El término constante es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Por eso una combinación consistente es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Simplificar</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La opción correcta es la alternativa A, porque representa la agrupación correcta de los términos de <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceA
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceA
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceB
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceB
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceC
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceC
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceD
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceD
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceB
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>